            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.4"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    University of Missouri 
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA</hi> 
                        <lb/>
                    65201
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE</hi>          
                        <lb/>
                    Department of English       
                        <lb/>
                    
                    231 Arts &amp; Science
                        <lb/>
                    Area 314 449-9756
                </fw>
            
                <opener>
                    <dateline>January 7, 1972</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am sure that you have received numerous copies of this article, but perhaps you may find use for one more. It is a most completely deserved tribute. Your wisdom<del>e</del> and goodness have been the high points of the educational experience of hundred of our students, including our son Ted.</p> 
                
                <p>I am interested in your suggestion about Don Drummond, and whenever I have a chance to forward it I will.</p> 
                
                <p>In closing I would like to tell you again how much of a privilege I have found it to known y u.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially yours</salute>
                
                    <signed>Edward H. Weatherly</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
